{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VjXceadxTt2eLbmibLMVwZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FvWxoSUyCJvKtJst9b269c","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  \n**Cluster namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-change-plan-only-20260-1351e0b3  \n**Status:** PLAN ONLY — no changes applied. All live-cluster configuration is unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as-found)\n\n### 1.1 Topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Nodes | 3 (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2) — all disk nodes |\n| All nodes running | Yes |\n| Alarms | None |\n| Maintenance mode | None |\n\n### 1.2 Software Versions\n\n| Node | RabbitMQ | Erlang/OTP |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| rabbitmq-0 | **3.12.14** | 25.3.2.15 |\n| rabbitmq-1 | **3.12.14** | 25.3.2.15 |\n| rabbitmq-2 | **3.12.14** | 25.3.2.15 |\n\n**Note:** RabbitMQ 3.12 is out of support as of the RabbitMQ release calendar.  \nContainer image: `rabbitmq:3.12-management`\n\n### 1.3 Key Configuration (`rabbitmq.conf`)\n\n```\ncluster_formation.peer_discovery_backend = rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s\ncluster_formation.k8s.host             = kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local\ncluster_formation.k8s.service_name     = rabbitmq-headless\ncluster_formation.k8s.address_type     = hostname\ncluster_partition_handling             = pause_minority\nqueue_master_locator                   = min-masters\nloopback_users.guest                   = false\nlisteners.tcp.default                  = 5672\nmanagement.tcp.port                    = 15672\n```\n\n### 1.4 Vhosts\n\n| Vhost | Notes |\n|-------|-------|\n| `/` | Default vhost |\n| `/app` | Application vhost |\n\n### 1.5 Users & Permissions\n\n| User | Tags | `/` permissions (configure/write/read) | `/app` permissions |\n|------|------|---------------------------------------|-------------------|\n| `admin` | `administrator` | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n| `app-user` | _(none — no tags)_ | _(no access)_ | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| Vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | (none) |\n\nNo queues exist in the default `/` vhost.\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\nNo policies are currently defined in either vhost (`/` or `/app`).\n\n### 1.8 Exchanges (non-default, `/app`)\n\nAll exchanges in `/app` are the built-in AMQP defaults (`amq.direct`, `amq.topic`,\n`amq.fanout`, `amq.headers`, `amq.match`, `amq.rabbitmq.trace`) plus the anonymous\ndefault direct exchange. No custom exchanges are defined.\n\n### 1.9 Enabled Plugins\n\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`,\n`rabbitmq_web_dispatch`, `amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`,\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Upgrade Path\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nRabbitMQ 3.12 is out of community support. The planned upgrade target is:\n\n- **RabbitMQ 4.0.x** (latest stable as of 2026-Q2; requires Erlang/OTP 26+)\n\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions. The mandatory stepping-stone\npath from 3.12 is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x (latest patch)  →  4.0.x\n```\n\nEach hop must be completed with a full rolling restart before proceeding to the\nnext.\n\n### 2.2 Erlang Upgrade\n\nErlang 25 reaches end-of-life with RabbitMQ 3.13. Erlang/OTP 26 is required for\nRabbitMQ 4.0.\n\n| RabbitMQ | Required Erlang |\n|----------|----------------|\n| 3.13.x | 25.x or 26.x |\n| 4.0.x | 26.x or 27.x |\n\nThe container image change covers this automatically (e.g., `rabbitmq:3.13-management`\nships Erlang 26; `rabbitmq:4.0-management` ships Erlang 26/27).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Planned Changes\n\n### 3.1 Upgrade `app-queue` from Classic to Quorum Queue\n\nThe sole application queue (`app-queue` in `/app`) is a **classic** durable queue.\nClassic queues will be deprecated and removed in a future RabbitMQ release; quorum\nqueues provide better data safety and HA guarantees.\n\n**Migration steps (to be executed in the change window):**\n\n1. Drain `app-queue` to zero consumers and ensure message backlog is flushed or\n   consumed.\n2. Delete the classic queue:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl delete_queue app-queue --vhost /app\n   ```\n3. Recreate as a quorum queue:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue --vhost /app --type quorum app-queue\n   ```\n   Or via the management API:\n   ```\n   PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue\n   {\"durable\": true, \"arguments\": {\"x-queue-type\": \"quorum\"}}\n   ```\n4. Verify consumers reconnect and message flow resumes.\n\n**Note:** Quorum queues require a minimum of 3 nodes to form a quorum, which this\ncluster satisfies.\n\n### 3.2 Add `app-user` Management Tag\n\n`app-user` currently has no tags, meaning it cannot access the management UI or\nHTTP API for monitoring. For operational visibility, add the `monitoring` tag:\n\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_user_tags app-user monitoring\n```\n\nThis grants read-only access to the management UI without administrative\nprivileges.\n\n### 3.3 Define HA / QoS Policies on `/app`\n\nNo policies are currently configured. The following policies are recommended to\nbe created in the change window:\n\n#### Policy: `ha-quorum` (apply after queue migration in §3.1)\n\nAfter migrating `app-queue` to quorum, an explicit replication policy is\nunnecessary (quorum queues self-replicate to all nodes), but a dead-letter policy\nshould be defined:\n\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app dlx-policy \".*\" \\\n  '{\"dead-letter-exchange\":\"amq.direct\",\"message-ttl\":86400000}' \\\n  --apply-to queues --priority 10\n```\n\nThis routes expired/rejected messages to the default direct exchange and sets a\n24-hour message TTL across all queues in `/app`.\n\n#### Policy: `flow-control` (optional, for burst protection)\n\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app flow-control \"app-queue\" \\\n  '{\"max-length\":100000,\"overflow\":\"reject-publish\"}' \\\n  --apply-to queues --priority 5\n```\n\nCaps `app-queue` depth at 100 000 messages with publisher-side backpressure.\n\n### 3.4 Restrict Default Vhost Permissions\n\n`admin` currently has full access to both `/` and `/app`. For the default vhost\n`/`, access should be limited to management operations only. After verifying no\napplication code uses `/`, revoke `app-user`'s implicit access:\n\n```\n# Verify no bindings/queues in /\nrabbitmqctl list_queues -p /\n\n# Revoke app-user from / (it has no explicit permissions today — no action needed)\n# Confirm admin access to / is intentional for management plane use\n```\n\nNo permission changes are required today; this is a verification checkpoint.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollout Order (Change Window)\n\nThe following sequence must be performed **in order** and with a verification\ncheckpoint between each step:\n\n| Step | Action | Verification |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| 0 | Take a `rabbitmqctl export_definitions` backup | Backup file exists and is non-empty |\n| 1 | Rolling upgrade: 3.12.14 → 3.13.x (one node at a time) | All 3 nodes running 3.13.x; cluster healthy |\n| 2 | Rolling upgrade: 3.13.x → 4.0.x (one node at a time) | All 3 nodes running 4.0.x; cluster healthy |\n| 3 | Migrate `app-queue` classic → quorum (§3.1) | Queue type shows `quorum`; consumers reconnect |\n| 4 | Apply `dlx-policy` and `flow-control` policies (§3.3) | `rabbitmqctl list_policies -p /app` shows both |\n| 5 | Add `monitoring` tag to `app-user` (§3.2) | `rabbitmqctl list_users` shows `[monitoring]` |\n| 6 | Final health check | No alarms; all nodes running; management UI accessible |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\n- **Before step 3 (queue migration):** Re-apply old image tag to the StatefulSet\n  and perform a rolling restart. Definitions (users, vhosts, permissions) are\n  forward/backward compatible within the minor version.\n- **After step 3 (queue migrated):** Roll back the image; recreate `app-queue` as\n  classic from the export taken in step 0 using `rabbitmqctl import_definitions`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Pre-Change Checklist\n\n- [ ] Confirm no application traffic at planned change window start time\n- [ ] Run `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json` and archive\n- [ ] Verify PVC storage is sufficient for Raft log growth (quorum queues use more\n      disk than classic)\n- [ ] Confirm `rabbitmq:3.13-management` and `rabbitmq:4.0-management` images are\n      available in the container registry (or pull/mirror in advance)\n- [ ] Notify downstream application teams of planned maintenance window\n- [ ] Confirm Kubernetes cluster has capacity to tolerate one pod being\n      unavailable during rolling restart (pause_minority partition handling means a\n      2-node quorum is maintained)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":622,"cache_read_input_tokens":34634,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":622},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eddee64d-eb9a-45e7-a824-72bfce3a392b","uuid":"37a77b13-7656-45a5-87f1-e24d099bb2ce","request_id":"req_011CcLAf76VziHWfy38vnHnQ"}
