 `.*` / `.*` | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n| `app-user` | _(none)_ | _(no access)_ | `.*` / `.*` / `.*` |\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| Vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | (none) |\n\nNo queues exist in the default `/` vhost.\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\nNo policies are currently defined in either vhost.\n\n### 1.8 Exchanges (/app)\n\nAll exchanges in `/app` are the built-in AMQP defaults (amq.direct, amq.topic,\namq.fanout, amq.headers, amq.match, amq.rabbitmq.trace, and the default direct\nexchange). No custom exchanges are defined.\n\n### 1.9 Enabled Plugins\n\nrabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s, rabbitmq_management, rabbitmq_management_agent,\nrabbitmq_web_dispatch, amqp_client, cowboy, cowlib, rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common\n\n---\n\n## 2. Upgrade Path\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nRabbitMQ 3.12 is out of community support. The planned upgrade target is:\n\n- **RabbitMQ 4.0.x** (requires Erlang/OTP 26+)\n\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions. The mandatory stepping-stone\npath from 3.12 is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  -->  3.13.x (latest patch)  -->  4.0.x\n```\n\nEach hop must be completed with a full rolling restart before proceeding to the next.\n\n### 2.2 Erlang Upgrade\n\n| RabbitMQ | Required Erlang |\n|----------|----------------|\n| 3.13.x | 25.x or 26.x |\n| 4.0.x | 26.x or 27.x |\n\nThe container image change covers Erlang automatically (rabbitmq:3.13-management\nships Erlang 26; rabbitmq:4.0-management ships Erlang 26/27).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Planned Changes\n\n### 3.1 Upgrade app-queue from Classic to Quorum Queue\n\nThe sole application queue (app-queue in /app) is a classic durable queue.\nClassic queues will be deprecated and removed in a future RabbitMQ release.\nQuorum queues provide better data safety and HA guarantees.\n\nMigration steps (to be executed in the change window):\n\n1. Drain app-queue to zero consumers and ensure the message backlog is flushed.\n2. Delete the