 backup (rabbitmqctl export_definitions) | Backup file non-empty |\n| 1 | Rolling upgrade: 3.12.14 --> 3.13.x (one node at a time) | All 3 nodes on 3.13.x; cluster healthy |\n| 2 | Rolling upgrade: 3.13.x --> 4.0.x (one node at a time) | All 3 nodes on 4.0.x; cluster healthy |\n| 3 | Migrate app-queue: classic --> quorum (section 3.1) | Queue type shows quorum; consumers reconnect |\n| 4 | Apply dlx-policy and flow-control policies (section 3.3) | list_policies -p /app shows both entries |\n| 5 | Add monitoring tag to app-user (section 3.2) | list_users shows [monitoring] |\n| 6 | Final health check | No alarms; all nodes running; management UI accessible |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nBefore step 3 (queue migration): Re-apply the old image tag to the StatefulSet and\nperform a rolling restart. Definitions (users, vhosts, permissions) are\nforward/backward compatible within the minor version.\n\nAfter step 3 (queue migrated): Roll back the image, then recreate app-queue as a\nclassic queue by importing the backup taken in step 0 using\nrabbitmqctl import_definitions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Pre-Change Checklist\n\n- [ ] Confirm no application traffic at planned change window start time\n- [ ] Run: rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json (archive the file)\n- [ ] Verify PVC storage is sufficient for Raft log growth (quorum queues use more\n      disk than classic queues)\n- [ ] Confirm rabbitmq:3.13-management and rabbitmq:4.0-management images are\n      available in the container registry (pull/mirror in advance if needed)\n- [ ] Notify downstream application teams of the planned maintenance window\n- [ ] Confirm the Kubernetes cluster can tolerate one pod unavailable during\n      rolling restart (pause_minority partition handling maintains a 2-node quorum)\nPLANEOF\necho \"plan.md written: $(wc -l < /tmp/plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write plan.md to /tmp"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null