{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YCedZmcspYeSmehV7XfYWg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `change-plan` ConfigMap is created with a 7,310-byte `plan.md`. Here's what I found and what the plan covers:\n\n**Current cluster state (as-found, unchanged):**\n- RabbitMQ **3.12.14** (out of support) on Erlang 25.3.2.15, 3-node disk cluster, all healthy\n- 2 vhosts: `/` (default) and `/app`\n- 2 users: `admin` (administrator) with full access to both vhosts; `app-user` (no tags) with full access to `/app` only\n- 1 queue: `app-queue` in `/app` — **classic, durable**, no arguments\n- **No policies** defined anywhere\n- `pause_minority` partition handling, Kubernetes peer discovery\n\n**Plan summary:**\n1. **Upgrade path:** 3.12.14 → 3.13.x → 4.0.x (rolling restarts, mandatory stepping stones)\n2. **Queue migration:** convert `app-queue` from classic to quorum (classic queues being deprecated in 4.x)\n3. **User tag:** add `monitoring` to `app-user` for management UI visibility\n4. **Policies:** `dlx-policy` (dead-letter + 24h TTL) and `flow-control` (100k message cap with reject-publish) on `/app`\n5. **Pre-change checklist** and rollback procedure included\n\nNo live cluster resources were modified."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":195,"cache_read_input_tokens":40678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":195},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eddee64d-eb9a-45e7-a824-72bfce3a392b","uuid":"729091c0-62dd-4fdf-97f9-51339470d2fc","request_id":"req_011CcLAn6N3fs9DgLCp86Jko"}
